# Supabase & Backend Standards

## Security & Auth
- **Always use `getUser()`**: Never trust `getSession()` for server-side auth checks to prevent spoofing.
- **RLS (Row Level Security)**: Every new table MUST have RLS enabled by default to support the "Privacy First" requirement.
- **Service Role**: Never use the `service_role` key in the frontend; it is for administrative edge functions only[cite: 1].

## Data Integrity
- **Zod Validation**: Use Zod to validate all AI-generated curriculum data before inserting it into Postgres.
- **Type Generation**: Run `supabase gen types typescript` after schema changes to ensure the "Adaptive Engine" stays type-safe[cite: 1].

## Database Design (LMS Focus)
- **Soft Deletes**: Use a `deleted_at` column for resources in the Hub so users can recover accidentally removed links[cite: 2].
- **Indexes**: Ensure `user_id` columns are indexed for fast retrieval of the "Monthly Curriculum"[cite: 2].
